The paper discusses the implementation of Binarized Neural Networks (BNNs) using Spin Torque Magnetoresistive Random Access Memory (ST-MRAM) without error correction. This work is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE), as well as emerging technologies (cs.ET) such as ST-MRAM. The paper also discusses the use of ST-MRAM for image recognition tasks (cs.AR), and the potential energy savings at the system level (cs.EM, cs.SY).
